# check-no-inline-date-bucket-math allowlist
# Expiry-policy: per-entry
#
# Plan PART 6, DoD#5: this allowlist is INTENTIONALLY EMPTY.
#
# The lists feature (apps/web/src/features/lists/**) must contain ZERO
# inline day-ms date math. All due-date bucketing and the 91-day review
# cadence are single-source-of-truth in:
#   - apps/web/src/shared/utils/dueDateBuckets.ts
#   - apps/web/src/shared/utils/reviewCycle.ts
# (both OUTSIDE this guard's scope, so they need no allowlist entry).
#
# An entry here would mean re-introducing inline bucket/cadence math —
# the exact drift class this guard exists to prevent. Before adding one:
#   1. Prefer extending the SSoT util instead.
#   2. If genuinely unavoidable, the entry MUST carry a # rationale and
#      an explicit operator authorization reference, and a follow-up
#      BUG-ID to remove it (no permanent allowlist debt — see CLAUDE.md
#      §15 / the M3 allowlist-as-architecture anti-pattern).
#
# Format: "<relpath>:<line>" (specific) or "<relpath>" (whole file).
